EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to repealing the call up provision following the granting of base station licenses.
EventItemMatterName: Repealing the call up provision following the granting of base station licenses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to evaluating the fiscal impact of rules.
EventItemMatterName: Evaluating the fiscal impact of rules.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to online submission of applications for permits, licenses and registrations and a single web portal for such applications
EventItemMatterName: Online submission of applications for permits, licenses and registrations and a single web portal for such applications.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring muni-meters receipts that can be affixed to motorcycles.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring muni-meters receipts that can be affixed to motorcycles.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation establishing a property tax credit for Class 2 cooperative and condominium buildings that are designated safe after a Façade Inspection Safety Program inspection.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing a property tax credit for Class 2 cooperative and condominium buildings that are designated safe after a Façade Inspection Safety Program inspection.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to informing parent teacher associations, community education councils, and principals of instructional arts education requirements.
EventItemMatterName: Informing parent teacher associations, community education councils, and principals of instructional arts education requirements.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to eliminating the passenger manifest and public support statement requirements for commuter vans, eliminating the requirement that commuter vans renew their license every six years, and repealing subdivision k of section 19-504.2
EventItemMatterName: Commuter Vans

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to submit to the council reports relating to motor vehicle stops.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the police department to submit to the council reports relating to motor vehicle stops.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the creation of a taskforce to study improving safety in homeless shelters.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a taskforce to study improving safety in homeless shelters.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation permitting voter registration forms utilized by agencies participating in the agency assisted voter registration program to code their registration forms, and for such codes to be withheld from public inspection.
EventItemMatterName: Permitting voter registration forms utilized by agencies participating in the agency assisted voter registration program to code their registration forms, and for such codes to be withheld from public inspection.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Human Resources Administration to explore obtaining state, federal and private funds for the Teen Relationship Abuse Prevention Program.
EventItemMatterName: Teen Relationship Abuse Prevention Program.
